content: As I wrote a few weeks ago, this is slightly more than a headache (and they didn’t just “slip through”). ,https://www.,vox.com/2018/7/9/17525,860/nazis-russell-walker-arthur-jones-republicans-illinois-north-carolina-virginia, ,…,https://,twitter.com/FoxNews/status,/1020389967024009223, ,…

“They didn’t just slip through”.  Your article also states the GOP is not supporting these individuals and R’s are outspoken about how bad these people are.  Are you trying to imply that the GOP tacitly approves of them because of Nixon’s Southern strategy from 70s?
Well, it's like France famously said in World War II: "The Nazis showed up and it's a real headache."
Remember that time when Robert Byrd was forced to resign his Senate seat because of his KKK past?
GOP know how to weed out our extremists.  Do the Dems?
